<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4588] The floating point arithmetic to validate memory allocation configurations need to be done as integers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4588</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The floating point arithmetic to validate memory allocation configurations need to be done as integers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On our cluster, we had block cache = 0.6 and memstore = 0.2.  It was saying this was &amp;gt; 0.8 when it is actually equal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Minor bug but annoying nonetheless.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
